\ slice! ( target tstart src sstart sstep slen -- target )
\ Copies slen elements: for i in 0..slen-1, target[tstart+i] = src[sstart+i*sstep].
\ Handles aliasing internally (in-place reverse and other overlapping cases).
\ Leaves target on stack.

\ Forward copy between distinct arrays
[ 0 0 0 0 0 ] 1 [ 10 20 30 ] 0 1 3 slice! . cr      \ [ 0 10 20 30 0 ]

\ Full copy at offset 0
[ 0 0 0 ] 0 [ 7 8 9 ] 0 1 3 slice! . cr             \ [ 7 8 9 ]

\ Reverse-direction read (negative step) between distinct arrays
[ 0 0 0 ] 0 [ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 4 -1 3 slice! . cr        \ [ 5 4 3 ]

\ slen = 0 is a no-op
[ 1 2 3 ] 0 [ 9 9 9 ] 0 1 0 slice! . cr             \ [ 1 2 3 ]

\ In-place reverse (source = target, sstep = -1, source starts at end of slice)
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 0 over 4 -1 5 slice! . cr             \ [ 5 4 3 2 1 ]

\ In-place reverse of a sub-range (positions 1..3)
[ 0 1 2 3 4 ] 1 over 3 -1 3 slice! . cr             \ [ 0 3 2 1 4 ]

\ In-place left-shift (source = target, sstart=1, sstep=1, write into 0..n-2)
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 0 over 1 1 4 slice! . cr              \ [ 2 3 4 5 5 ]

\ Sets via slice — source can be a set (items in sorted order)
[ 0 0 0 ] 0 < 3 1 2 > 0 1 3 slice! . cr             \ [ 1 2 3 ]

\ Stride > 1 — take every other element
[ 0 0 0 ] 0 [ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 0 2 3 slice! . cr       \ [ 1 3 5 ]

\ Errors

\ Target out of bounds
[ 1 2 3 ] 1 [ 9 9 9 ] 0 1 3 slice!

\ Source out of bounds
[ 0 0 0 ] 0 [ 1 2 ] 0 1 3 slice!

\ Negative source index after stride
[ 0 0 0 ] 0 [ 1 2 3 ] 0 -1 3 slice!

\ Negative length
[ 0 0 0 ] 0 [ 1 2 3 ] 0 1 -1 slice!

\ Non-array source
[ 0 0 0 ] 0 42 0 1 3 slice!

\ Non-array target
"hello" 0 [ 1 2 3 ] 0 1 3 slice!
